{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b2a50caf-23d0-414d-b0a0-7fcfa4c9ceea","content":"The issue is the **file compilation order** in the `.fsproj`. F# requires files to be listed in dependency order. `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` is listed first.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_019zZhyEtU8AA7uKmWCiYdRi","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Fixing F# file order"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01Dd6XhTLjibC5fTZEZ7XG3J","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-ac104b7c812c4407876dfc91d6f92d56/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />","new_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-ac104b7c812c4407876dfc91d6f92d56/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"1e81ef5d-6614-40bb-a135-dea8adf0525b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file compilation order matters — files can only reference modules/types defined in files listed **before** them in the `.fsproj`. \n\nThe `.fsproj` currently has:\n1. `Services.fs` — depends on `Domain.fs` (opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`)\n2. `Domain.fs` — defines the types\n3. `Program.fs` — depends on both\n\n`Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`. The fix is to swap the order so `Domain.fs` comes first.","outputTokens":418,"requestId":"C78D:283B0A:F259F6:131413A:69FFD738"},"id":"f5794f2d-a8a5-4279-a4f1-abe172b0d42c","timestamp":"2026-05-10T00:54:24.272Z","parentId":"ff11e900-6d06-4597-979d-3b4faec924bb"}
